Class: CS-341: "Modern Web Applications"
Assignment: Shark Tank Final Project
Date: 23 March 2026
Author: Samantha Robinson
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
FitMatch is a full-stack web application that allows users to upload clothing items, organize a digital closet, generate outfits, and save favorite looks. The system combines user-uploaded wardrobe data with automated outfit generation to create a personalized styling experience. The platform also includes a community feature, where users can view outfits favorited by others.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Features: 
- User Authentication: Register and login with JWT authentication
- Digital Closet: Upload clothing items (tops, bottoms, shoes)
- Outfit Generation: Generates outfits using user’s actual uploaded clothes
- Favorites: Save favorite outfits to profile and share to community feed
- Community Feed: Displays all users' favorite outfits
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Frontend & Backend
Frontend: React (Vite), JavaScript, CSS, React Router
Backend: Node.js, Express, MongoDB + Mongoose, JWT Authentication, Multer (file uploads), Sharp (image processing)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The program can be used as follows from the terminal: 
cd backend
npm start
cd frontend
npm run dev
Note: npm may need to be installed
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Deployment Link: 
https://shark-tank-final-project.vercel.app/